04288nam a22005535i 9780773553101DE-B159720240306124542.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20182018xxc    fo  d z      eng d  a97807735531017 a10.1515/97807735531012doi  a(DE-B1597)656290  a(OCoLC)1031374176  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxccCA 4aTP573.5.M645 7aBIO0030002bisacsh04a663/.420922231 aAntoniou, Helen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aBack to Beer.and Hockey :bThe Story of Eric Molson /cHelen Antoniou. 1aMontreal ;aKingston ;aLondon ;aChicago : bMcGill-Queen's University Press, c[2018] 4c©2018  a1 online resource :b91 b&w images  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFront Matter -- tContents -- tThe Age-Old Recipe -- tThe Call to Adventure -- tGrowing Up in Eric's World -- tMeeting the Heroine -- tBrewing Beer at Molson -- tBecoming the Boss -- tBuying Back the Canadiens -- tThe Call to Adventure -- tCrossing the Threshold -- tNavigating the Road of Trials -- tWelcoming Ian into the Fold -- tMaking Molson a Brewery Again -- tThe Molson Family Principles -- tFacing Setbacks -- tConfronting Boardroom Politics -- tThe Return -- tTaking the High Road -- tRelaying the Elixir to Generation VII -- tAcknowledgments -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aTo most Canadians, the Molson name is part of the very fabric of Canada. Since 1786, when John Molson founded his first brewery in Montreal, it has become synonymous with beer, hockey, and philanthropy. Few realize, however, how close the family came in recent years to losing control of the enterprise. Back to Beer.and Hockey offers intimate details of the life and work of Eric Molson, who not only saved the company, but positioned it to thrive as a global brewery into the twenty-first century. With unprecedented access to the Molson family, Helen Antoniou traces Eric Molson's evolution from a young brewmaster captivated by the chemistry of beer-making to chairman of Molson. Quiet by nature, he had to confront big egos, navigate complex boardroom politics, and even battle a disruptive cousin who tried to push him out of the way. Antoniou's carefully researched account details how the introverted Eric overcame his aversion to conflict to take the company from a failing conglomerate back to its core business of beer, eventually turning it into one of the world's leading brewers. Today, he has passed the torch to his sons, the seventh generation, but his steadfast vision prevails. An absorbing account of one man's struggle at the helm of an international brewing giant, Back to Beer.and Hockey shows how Eric Molson's guiding principles influenced the future of Molson – both the enterprise and the family.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBeer industryzCanada. 0aBrewerszCanadavBiography. 0aBrewing industryzCanada. 0aBusinesspeoplezCanadavBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Business.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780773553101?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773553101423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773553101/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles